Comment:
Hi everyone!

I finally decided to join the Traxler Mini-tournament and managed to finish my first game in it with a win today.  It was amazing just how it seemed to all come out of nowhere!

3. ...... Nf6 - this move characterises the Two Knights Defense.  My next move which is Ng5 hits out at the weak f7 square and threatens a nasty Q + R fork on it.  The move d5 is normally played but here a counter-attack is spawned by the developing move Bc5 hitting out at f2.

7. ...... Ng4 - what's this?  His knight is en prise.  Can I safely nab it?  On analysis I decided it was safe to do so.  In fact my opponent anticipated this capture because he put in the sneaky move d6 as a conditional!  No doubt he was hoping I would not notice Glenda was en prise!
